Different educational texts about pre-school education and early years' teachers' profession, teacher training practice in Estonia and elsewhere, most important issues, strategies, learning styles and methods, learning through playing, inclusive learning  and the themes chosen by students are treated. Discussions on educational issues are initiated. Different strategies are used: discussions, case studies, presentations, writing annotations in order to enrich both oral and written expression. Interactive approach and social learning are applied.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To enlarge students` vocabulary and develop their grammar skills on B1 language level in order to prepare students for independent work with literature in the field of pre-school and general education.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the module the student: - knows essential vocabulary in the field of education and comprehends speciality-related texts; - discusses educational issues within the range of the vocabulary acquired; - can summarize and paraphrase educational texts; - compiles and makes an oral presentation on speciality-related literature; - analyses and gives feedback on peers' presentations.
